This paper deals with privacy-sensitive users and their control over tracking, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the economic impact of ad-blocking, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or social and information networks (cs.SI). The implementation of the proposed solution as a Google Chrome extension could fall under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) or cybernetics (cs.CY).
